Orderless ([https://github.com/oantolin/orderless GitHub], [https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/orderless.html GNU ELPA]) provides a ''completion style'' "for matching regexps in any order".

It can be used together with:
* The default Emacs completion, IcompleteMode, or [[Vertico]].
* [[Consult]]'s `consult-completion-in-region'
* CompanyMode
* [[Corfu]]
* [[IvyCounselSwiper|Ivy]]

